-- AngloGold Shut Its Siguiri Mine in Guinea For Two Days Because of Protests
-- B y   C a r l i   L o u r e n s
-- 2011-01-28T05:28:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-01-28/anglogold-shut-its-siguiri-mine-in-guinea-for-two-days-because-of-protests.html
  AngloGold Ashanti Ltd . said it halted
it Siguiri mine in  Guinea  for two days earlier this week as a
‘precautionary’ measure after a protest started.  Operations were suspended pending discussions between
demonstrators and the provincial governor, AngloGold said in an
e-mailed response to a query today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Carli Lourens at 
 clourens@bloomberg.net  